sentences: Ayaka Hirahara (平原 綾香, Hirahara Ayaka, born May 9, 1984) is a Japanese pop singer.
She was affiliated with the Dreamusic label until 2013 when she moved to Universal Music Japan.
Her first single, "Jupiter", was released in Japan in December 2003, and went on to be one of the biggest selling singles of 2004.
Her first single, "Jupiter", was released in Japan in December 2003, and went on to be one of the biggest selling singles of 2004.
She then released a series of classical themed My Classics albums from 2009 to 2011.
She continued her career on Dreamusic until 2013.
She released another single, titled "Shine - 未来へかざす火のように" on November 13, 2013.
She released her debut album with Universal on December 4, 2013.
Hirahara's song Reset, from the album Yottsu no L was used in Capcom's 2006 title, Ōkami, as the ending song.
On November 1, Universal revealed the track list of Ayaka's next album (one of which is her cover version of "I Dreamed a Dream" from Les Misérables ).
She started playing saxophone when she was 13 years old, then learned classical saxophone at Senzoku Gakuen High School.
Ayaka was a member of the Matsuyama Ballet for 11 years, beginning at age 6.
Currently, she is studying in the Faculty of Jazz majoring in saxophone at Senzoku Gakuen College of Music.
